block content

  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          nav(aria-label="breadcrumb")
            ol.breadcrumb.mb-3
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/") Home
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/blog.html") Blog
              li.breadcrumb-item.active.text-white(aria-current="page") Inpatient vs Outpatient
          h1.display-5.fw-bold Inpatient vs. Outpatient Rehab in Spokane: Which is Right for You?
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 Understanding the levels of care available in the Inland Northwest to help you make an informed choice.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 9 min read

  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          p.lead.mt-5
            | When you decide to get help for substance abuse in Spokane, one of the first questions the intake coordinator will ask is: "Are you looking for inpatient or outpatient care?" For many, the difference isn't clear. Choosing the right level of care is critical for both the safety of your detox and the long-term success of your sobriety.

          hr.my-5

          h2.mt-4 
            i.bi.bi-house-heart.text-primary.me-2
            | Inpatient (Residential) Treatment
          p
            | Inpatient rehab involves living at a treatment facility 24/7. This provides a controlled, drug-free environment and constant medical and emotional support.
          ul
            li
              strong Best for:
              |  Moderate to severe addictions, those with high relapse risks, or anyone whose home environment is currently unsafe or unstable.
            li
              strong Local Spokane Options:
              |  Facilities like **American Behavioral Health Systems (ABHS)** and **Spokane Falls Recovery Center** offer residential stays.
            li
              strong Duration:
              |  Typically 30, 60, or 90 days.

          h2.mt-5 
            i.bi.bi-calendar-check.text-primary.me-2
            | Outpatient Treatment (IOP/OP)
          p
            | Outpatient care allows you to live at home while attending treatment several times a week. **Intensive Outpatient Programs (IOP)** usually require 9–15 hours of therapy per week.
          ul
            li
              strong Best for:
              |  Those with strong support systems at home, mild to moderate addictions, or individuals who cannot leave work or family responsibilities for months.
            li
              strong Local Spokane Options:
              |  **Frontier Behavioral Health**, **The Native Project**, and several private clinics offer robust IOP services.
            li
              strong Duration:
              |  Ranges from 3 months to over a year, depending on progress.

          h2.mt-5 
            i.bi.bi-cash-coin.text-primary.me-2
            | Cost and Coverage in Washington State
          p
            | In Washington, Medicaid (Apple Health) covers both inpatient and outpatient treatment if it is deemed medically necessary. Private insurance also usually covers both, though inpatient stays often require "prior authorization" from the insurance company.

          hr.my-5

          .card.border-0.shadow.text-center.p-5.mb-4(style="border-radius: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d6efd11 0%, #0d6efd22 100%);")
            i.bi.bi-hospital.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
            h3.fw-bold Not sure which one you need?
            p.text-muted.mb-4
              | You don't have to guess. Most Spokane clinics offer free "assessments" to determine the appropriate level of care for you.
            .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-3.justify-content-center
              a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/addiction-treatments-support.html")
                i.bi.bi-search.me-2
                | View Treatment Directory
